Analysis of the Target Image  
•  Total Block Count & Layering  
  -  The finished tower uses 9 total blocks.  
  -  From bottom to top, it can be viewed in “layers” as follows:  
    1)  Bottom layer: one wide, flat yellow rectangular block.  
    2)  Above it: two tall orange cylinders (side‐by‐side).  
    3)  A second yellow rectangular block bridging across the tops of the cylinders.  
    4)  Three vertical green rectangular blocks standing on that middle yellow block.  
    5)  A third yellow rectangular block resting on top of the green pillars.  
    6)  Finally, one orange triangular “roof” block perched on top.  

•  Spatial Relationships  
  -  The single yellow base block sits flat on the ground.  
  -  The two orange cylinders stand upright on the base, spaced so that a second yellow block can lie across their tops.  
  -  Three vertical green blocks are then placed on that middle yellow platform, forming three “posts” that support the third yellow beam.  
  -  The orange triangular block (the “roof”) sits centered on the top yellow block.  

Selection of Dictionary Blocks  
Match each shape/color/orientation exactly as shown (no rotating beyond what the dictionary images allow):  
1)  Three yellow horizontal rectangular bars → Block index 4 (used three times)  
2)  Two orange vertical cylinders → Block index 8 (used twice)  
3)  Three green vertical rectangular pillars → Block index 2 (used three times)  
4)  One orange “roof”‐shaped triangular prism → Block index 11 (used once)  

Proposed Assembly Order  
{
  Step1: Move block with index 4         (place the bottom yellow rectangular base)  
  Step2: Move block with index 8         (add first orange cylinder on the base)  
  Step3: Move block with index 8         (add second orange cylinder on the base)  
  Step4: Move block with index 4         (lay the middle yellow rectangular block atop the cylinders)  
  Step5: Move block with index 2         (place first green vertical pillar)  
  Step6: Move block with index 2         (place second green vertical pillar)  
  Step7: Move block with index 2         (place third green vertical pillar)  
  Step8: Move block with index 4         (add the top yellow rectangular block across the green pillars)  
  Step9: Move block with index 11        (finish with the orange triangular roof piece)  
}
